  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Contextual_shape_positioning_arm  Entity: Component_representation_inclusion
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Contextual_shape_positioning_arm.Contextual_shape_representation_inclusion">
A <b>Contextual_shape_representation_inclusion</b> is the association of the contextual shape of a product version with its positioned representation.
<p>
The position is expressed in the coordinate space of a geometric model representing the shape of the product version that uses the product version whose contextual shape is considered.
</p>
<p>
The positioned representation defines the representation of the contextual shape in that position.
</p>

</ext_description>

   <ext_description linkend="Contextual_shape_positioning_arm.Contextual_shape_representation_inclusion.contextual_shape">
the <express_ref linkend="shape_property_assignment:arm:Shape_property_assignment_arm.Contextual_item_shape"/> of the product version that is represented and located.
	 </ext_description>
	 
   <ext_description linkend="Contextual_shape_positioning_arm.Contextual_shape_representation_inclusion.context_representation">
the <express_ref linkend="representation_schema:ir_express:representation_schema.representation"/> in which the representation of the contextual shape is characterized.
	 </ext_description>

   <ext_description linkend="Contextual_shape_positioning_arm.Contextual_shape_representation_inclusion.positioned_representation">
the instance that contains the representation of the contextual shape in the context representation.
	 </ext_description>

	   <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
	   Schema: Elemental_geometric_shape_arm  Entity: Mapping_based_template_instance 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Contextual_shape_positioning_arm.Mapping_based_template_instance">
A <b>Mapping_based_template_instance</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Detailed_geometric_model_element"/>.  It is the replication of a <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Geometric_model">Geometric_model</express_ref>.
The replication transformation is defined by a <express_ref linkend="contextual_shape_positioning:arm:Contextual_shape_positioning_arm.Mapping_based_template_instance.source"/> <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Axis_placement"/> and a <express_ref linkend="contextual_shape_positioning:arm:Contextual_shape_positioning_arm.Mapping_based_template_instance.target"/> that may be an <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Axis_placement"/> or a <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.cartesian_transformation"/>.
<p>In the first case, the transformation shall be computed as the isometric transformation that maps:</p>
<ul>
<li>the <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Axis_placement.origin"/> of the <express_ref linkend="contextual_shape_positioning:arm:Contextual_shape_positioning_arm.Mapping_based_template_instance.source"/> onto the <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Axis_placement.origin"/> of the <express_ref linkend="contextual_shape_positioning:arm:Contextual_shape_positioning_arm.Mapping_based_template_instance.target"/>;</li>
<li>the <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Axis_placement.x_axis"/> of the <express_ref linkend="contextual_shape_positioning:arm:Contextual_shape_positioning_arm.Mapping_based_template_instance.source"/> onto the <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Axis_placement.x_axis"/> of the <express_ref linkend="contextual_shape_positioning:arm:Contextual_shape_positioning_arm.Mapping_based_template_instance.target"/>;</li>
<li>the <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Axis_placement.y_axis"/> of the <express_ref linkend="contextual_shape_positioning:arm:Contextual_shape_positioning_arm.Mapping_based_template_instance.source"/> onto the <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Axis_placement.y_axis"/> of the <express_ref linkend="contextual_shape_positioning:arm:Contextual_shape_positioning_arm.Mapping_based_template_instance.target"/>.</li>
</ul>
<p>In the second case, the transformation shall be computed as the transformation that maps:</p>
<ul>
<li>the <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Axis_placement.origin"/> of the <express_ref linkend="contextual_shape_positioning:arm:Contextual_shape_positioning_arm.Mapping_based_template_instance.source"/> onto the translation point of the <express_ref linkend="contextual_shape_positioning:arm:Contextual_shape_positioning_arm.Mapping_based_template_instance.target"/>;</li>
<li>the <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Axis_placement.x_axis"/> of the <express_ref linkend="contextual_shape_positioning:arm:Contextual_shape_positioning_arm.Mapping_based_template_instance.source"/> onto the first element of the <express_ref linkend="contextual_shape_positioning:arm:Contextual_shape_positioning_arm.Mapping_based_template_instance.target"/> of the <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Axis_placement_mapping.target"/>;</li>
<li>the <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Axis_placement.y_axis"/> of the <express_ref linkend="contextual_shape_positioning:arm:Contextual_shape_positioning_arm.Mapping_based_template_instance.source"/> onto the second element of the <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Cartesian_transformation_2d.multiplication_matrix"/> of the <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Axis_placement_mapping.target"/>.</li>
<li>in case the transformation is a 3D transformation, the normalised vector product of the <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Axis_placement.x_axis"/> and the <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Axis_placement.y_axis"/> of the <express_ref linkend="contextual_shape_positioning:arm:Contextual_shape_positioning_arm.Mapping_based_template_instance.source"/> onto the third element of the <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Cartesian_transformation_2d.multiplication_matrix"/> of the <express_ref linkend="contextual_shape_positioning:arm:Contextual_shape_positioning_arm.Mapping_based_template_instance.target"/>.</li>
</ul>
<note number="1">
In the case where the <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Geometric_coordinate_space"/> of the replicated model is not the same as the <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Geometric_coordinate_space"/> in which the <express_ref linkend="contextual_shape_positioning:arm:Contextual_shape_positioning_arm.template_instance"/> is founded, 
care shall be taken of any difference in the length units of both the instances of <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Geometric_coordinate_space"/>, as unit conversion may be required.
</note>
        
<example>
In a technical drawing of a mechanical part with several identical drilling holes, 
the hole geometry, is represented by a circle named 'annotated drilling hole'. 
This representation of the hole is replicated several times 
at different locations by corresponding <express_ref linkend="contextual_shape_positioning:arm:Contextual_shape_positioning_arm.template_instance"/> objects.  
</example>

<note number="2">The mapping-table defines two interpretations for this ARM entity. The first one uses the MIM entity <express_ref linkend="representation_schema:ir_express:representation_schema.mapped_item"/> which uses the same principle to define the transformation as the <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Axis_placement_mapping"/> 
and <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Axis_placement_transformation_mapping"/> entities. The second one uses the MIM entity <express_ref linkend="representation_schema:ir_express:representation_schema.representation_relationship_with_transformation"/>

. Although this latter entity is not semantically equivalent to the ARM entity, the second 
interpretation is kept because of its use in some implementations.
</note> 
   </ext_description>

